## What I Learned:
- A network is simply a collection of connected devices [citation:1]
- The Internet is a giant network made up of many smaller networks [citation:2]
- IP addresses identify devices logically and can change
- MAC addresses are physical identifiers burned into network interfaces
- MAC addresses can be spoofed (changed virtually) [citation:3]
- Ping uses ICMP protocol to test connectivity between devices

